if else:
✅ IF-ELSE IN C:

👉 Explanation:
The if-else statement allows decision-making in programs. It executes one block if a condition is true, and another if false.

👉 Syntax:
```c
if(condition) {
    // Code when condition is true
} else {
    // Code when condition is false
}
```

👉 Example:
```c
#include<stdio.h>
int main() {
    int age = 18;
    if(age >= 18) {
        printf("You are eligible to vote.\n");
    } else {
        printf("You are not eligible to vote.\n");
    }
    return 0;
}
```

👉 Assignment:
1️⃣ Write a program to check if a number is positive or negative.
2️⃣ Write a program to check if a number is even or odd.

ternary:
✅ TERNARY OPERATOR IN C:

👉 Explanation:
A shorthand form of if-else. Used when there is a single line decision.

👉 Syntax:
```c
condition ? true_expression : false_expression;
```

👉 Example:
```c
#include<stdio.h>
int main() {
    int num = 5;
    (num % 2 == 0) ? printf("Even\n") : printf("Odd\n");
    return 0;
}
```

👉 Assignment:
1️⃣ Use ternary to find the greatest of two numbers.
2️⃣ Use ternary to check if a number is positive or negative.

switch:
✅ SWITCH STATEMENT IN C:

👉 Explanation:
Switch is used when we want to perform different actions based on different constant values of a variable.

👉 Syntax:
```c
switch(expression) {
    case value1:
        // code
        break;
    case value2:
        // code
        break;
    default:
        // code
}
```

👉 Example:
```c
#include<stdio.h>
int main() {
    int day = 3;
    switch(day) {
        case 1:
            printf("Monday\n");
            break;
        case 2:
            printf("Tuesday\n");
            break;
        case 3:
            printf("Wednesday\n");
            break;
        default:
            printf("Invalid day\n");
    }
    return 0;
}
```

👉 Assignment:
1️⃣ Write a program using switch to display month name when month number (1-12) is entered.
2️⃣ Create a calculator using switch for operations (+, -, *, /).
